text: Columbia County is a county in the U.S. state of Washington. The county seat is Dayton. 3,952 people lived there at the 2020 census which makes it the third-least populous county in Washington. The county was created out of Walla Walla County on November 11, 1875 and is named after the Columbia River. == References == Category:1875 establishments in the United States Category:1870s establishments in Washington (state) Category:Washington (state) counties
title: Columbia County, Washington
